<br>
There seems to be a hard cap in the game (I suspect due to the need to animate the attacker for each attack) of one attack every 2 seconds.<br>
<br>
Your fists already DO that, once your physinit is up to 150 at max aggro, so, any additional weapon merely 'steals' attack slots from your fists.   The more your weapon hits, the less your fists do.<br>
<br>
When I tried it, I was getting 7 fist attacks per 15 seconds (between brawls).<br>
<br>
Using a weapon that turned out to do 3 attacks per brawl, yep, I got 4 fist attacks per brawl.<br>
<br>
This does vary somewhat, depending on the exact timing as the attack timers fight it out, but in general, unless they make some attacks not animate the attacker, forget 'more' attacks. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/ucson777.showPublicProfile?language=EN>cson777</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Training Dummy</span><br>  Posts: 62<br> <font color=#660000>(12/13/01 9:02:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1484.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Interview with CZ (12/12/2001)</span><hr size=1> Does this apply to MOBs? Have you seen the attach bar on a Scorpiod or Greater Anun? My physical init is around 650, and even on full aggro, their attack bar is twice as fast as mine. <br>
<br>
Here's the problem I see: Our fists are naturally slow. At lower levels, it's great because it allows us to attack quickly. However, our fists max out at 1/1 attack/recharge. And a rifle with 2.0/3.0 and a lot higher damage can get to 1.0/1.0 at higher levels when you have 800+ range init. So basically, at lvl 103, I'm hitting for 109 every two seconds, and a Yellow Laseraim is hitting me for 170 every two seconds; and he's got three or four times the HPs that I have.<br>
